# Security Considerations

## API Key Handling

- User API keys (OpenAI, Anthropic) encrypted at rest with AES-256
- Keys only decrypted server-side for API calls
- Never expose keys to client bundle
- Show only last 4 chars in UI (`keyHint` field)

## Widget Security

- Widget keys are public (embedded in sites)
- REST API keys are secret (server-to-server)
- Rate limiting on widget endpoint:
  - 10 submissions/minute per IP
  - 100 submissions/day per widget
- Honeypot field for spam detection

## Authentication

- Clerk handles all auth
- Protected routes redirect unauthenticated users
- Session tokens passed to Convex for auth
- Always check `ctx.auth.getUserIdentity()` in mutations/queries

## Webhooks

- HMAC signatures on all webhook payloads
- Verify signature before processing
- Log all webhook attempts

## Data Protection

- GDPR compliance features implemented
- Data export for submitters
- Data deletion requests supported
- Anonymization preserves feedback while removing PII

## Environment Variables

Never commit secrets. Required env vars:

```bash
# Convex
CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=xxx
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=xxx

# Clerk
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_xxx
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_xxx

# Stripe
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx

# Resend
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxx

# Encryption
ENCRYPTION_KEY=xxx  # For API key encryption
```

## Code Review Checklist

- [ ] No credentials in client bundle
- [ ] Auth checks on all protected endpoints
- [ ] Input validation on user data
- [ ] Rate limiting on public endpoints
- [ ] Encrypted storage for sensitive data
- [ ] HMAC verification on webhooks
